key_points.allegations: Professional misconduct under Legal Practitioners and Bar Councils Act, 1973.
key_points.respondent_defense: Cases were independent, no conflict of interest, complaint termed frivolous.
key_points.disciplinary_committee_findings: Two cases were distinct with separate causes of action. Respondent acted in private capacity as a witness.
key_points.tribunal_decision: Complaint dismissed due to lack of substance and malice by complainant.

legal_references: Legal Practitioners and Bar Councils Act, 1973
Pakistan Legal Practitioners and Bar Councils Rules, 1976
costs_payment_instructions: Deposit with Secretary, N.-W.F.P. Bar Council, Peshawar. Payable to respondent under proper receipt.
